DENGUE VIRUSES: REAGENTS AVAILABLE
**********************************
A ProMED-mail post
Date: Wed, 29 Oct 1997 09:44:21 -0500
From: German Roges <groges@ipk.sld.cu>

The WHO Collaborating Center for Viral Diseases, Institute of Tropical
Medicine "Pedro Kouri" at La Habana, Cuba, announces to interested people
that it is able to supply laboratory reagents for the diagnosis of
dengue virus infections. These reagents can be supplied to laboratories
and epidemiology centers involved in activities to control the epidemic
currently affecting the Latin American continent.
These reagents may be antigens for hemagglutination, antisera, conjugates,
monoclonal antibodies against the four serotypes or a set of reagents that
permits the detection of specific IgM antibodies.
Please address any request or questions to the address below.
--
Dr. German Roges
Institute of Tropical Medicine "Pedro Kouri"
La Habana, Cuba
e-mail: <groges@ipk.sld.cu>
[I know these reagents by reputation only but I have heard they are
excellent and of high titer and specificity. For further information,
please contact Dr. Roges directly. - Mod.CHC]
..................................................chc/es
